<div id="review_2305469086" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2305469086" />
    <a title="Megan Knippenberg" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13175528-megan-knippenberg"><img alt="Megan Knippenberg" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1355199831p2/13175528.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2305469086?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Megan Knippenberg" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Megan Knippenberg" href="/user/show/13175528-megan-knippenberg">Megan Knippenberg</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2305469086" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9165142748562634418">I love the central idea of this book that all you need to change your life is a little perspective. The story is neat, and there is a lot of good advice packed into this little book. The only thing keeping it from getting five stars is that sometimes the wisdom in the story seems forced.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


